# Project Architecture

This solution follows Clean Architecture with CQRS per microservice.

## Layer structure

```
ServiceName/
├── Domain/          # Entities, Shared (Result, Failure), Exceptions
├── Application/     # Commands, Queries, Messaging, Interfaces, DTOs
├── Infrastructure/  # Data (DbContext, Repositories), Middleware, Migrations
└── Presentation/    # Endpoints, Models, Profiles, Extensions
```

## Key conventions

- Use the `Result<T>` / `Result` wrapper for all command/query responses
- Use `IEndpoint` + minimal APIs, not controllers, for new endpoints
- Register endpoints via `AddEndpoints()` / `MapEndpoints()` extensions
- Use MediatR for all command/query dispatch
- Use AutoMapper for mapping between Models, Commands, and DTOs
- PostgreSQL via Npgsql + EF Core for persistence
- Each service has its own database
